	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="/images/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Being an avid roleplayer for years, perhaps I can settle a little dispute over the bow issue.  The paladin is, as we all know, a knight, a champion of honor and chivalry.  Chivalry dictates that all enemies must be vanquished in a fair and just way, that allows both sides equal ground and a chance to win the contest.  The bow was not used by knights, or paladins, at all.  The bow is considered cowardly, due to the fact that one can be shot with an arrow with little or no risk to the archer.  Knights would consider using a bow equivalent to a drive by shooting in modern times.  The archer has no risk, and therefore is unfair in his attack on the intended target.  I am a paladin myself, but for the record I do use a longbow, due to it's extreme usefulness in the game and otherwise.  However I am aware of it's inaccuracy for paladins to use, and am content to deal with that knowledge for however long my arrow supply lasts.<BR>
<BR>
- Dareshine Sapphire<BR>
  9th Level - Knights of the Holy Order<BR>
  Freeport
				</font>
			</td>

